messages.text: Is that supposed to mean something?
Would you stop texting me, please!
If this is you Johnny, it’s a stupid prank and I don’t get it.
Is that supposed to be something of a count down?
The actions you committed have caused the expiration of your life to come sooner.
The actions of the night of November 18.
How do you know about that?
I don’t believe anything that you’re saying.
You are currently walking southbound on Main Street.
If you do not change your actions, you will die.
You’re just trying to scare me.
If you stop walking and look to your left, a red car will pass by almost hitting a stray dog.
You can’t predict something like that.
How did you know that was going to happen?
I would not concern myself with who I am but rather what you must do.
What do I have to do?
That night. What you did. Do you remember?
Yes. My friends and I snuck into a department store and took some items.
You left the back door unlocked. This caused a deranged man to get possession of a kitchen knife that will be used on your friend.
How do I stop it from happening?
Are you saying I have 3 minutes left?
I’m running to her house now!
I’m right in front of her house!
I can hear her coming. Hold on!
I’m inside with her! Now what?
You have to keep her safe.
And how do I do that?
The cops will get him. I can hear the sirens.
I heard the door break open! Tell me what to do!
Keep your body pressed against the door and use your feet to push against the sink.
He will not be strong enough to get in.
I hear him coming up the steps!
I’m against the door. He’s trying to push it open.
He’s yelling at us to open the door.
The police will be there in one minute and forty-two seconds.
He’s kicking the door and it’s slightly opening!
Your friend will live to see another day.
You’re the one who made up for her actions.
I swear I’m never going to do anything like that again.
How do I even explain this to Ronda?
I will speak to her soon. Right now, enjoy this moment.
I don’t know who you are but I am grateful.
What is that count down for?
You have to trust yourself. Everything you’ve done was perfect.
I can hear the cops pulling in.
They cannot save your destiny. Only you can.
Tell me why do I have to do anything more.
Something as simple as the opening of a door can lead to the most significant changes in our lives and in the lives of others.
You want me to step out?
And be sure to shut the bathroom door behind you.
The door is open. I’m going out.
Yes. I’m behind the bathroom door.
That man appeared out of nowhere and killed Emily!
He’s trying to get into the bathroom.
The cops are inside the house.
I heard the window break. I think the man escaped.
Ronda, I need you to know something.
Ronda, I need you to type “bye bye”.
The cops are calling out to me.
ALL TEXTS FROM THIS CHAIN HAVE BEEN DELETED.
